init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the wolf said, "what are you laughing about?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And Arthur said, "because I have made my house out of a nuclear waste material.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the wolf was like, "I don't get it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Why would you make your house out of nuclear waste?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And Arthur said, "because it is the strongest material there is.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I mean it's so strong, that you can't even blow it down!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So the wolf gathered all of his huffing and puffing into one big gulp, and he took a big old blow at Arthur's house

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But when he blew, Arthur's house didn't budge an inch.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was so mad, and he tried again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He kept trying and trying but he just couldn't blow the house down.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So he kept puffing and huffing until he thought that his head was going to explode.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Arthur, who was really enjoying this, said to the wolf "wow, you are going to have a really bad headache when you calm

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Do you want me to get you an aspirin?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was really determined to get into this house, and he tried again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He threw the grenade at Arthur's house and he blew his own brains out.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He knew that the wolf had not succeeded in blowing down his house, but he also did not want to stay there because it was a radioactive pigsty

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So he started to look for a new place to live.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He thought and he thought and he thought.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And then he had an idea.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 93rd little pig went to the nearest Wal-Mart.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He found some steel-toed rubber boots, some heavy-duty gloves, hardhats, and finally he ran into the paint department where he

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: With those items in hand, he began to build a house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He used the lead paint to coat the foundation of his new home, and he coated it heavily.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He coated it so heavily that it looked like an old Victorian house with gingerbread, but more industrial.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Matty and Arthur enjoyed living together in the new house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It had the hallmarks of a good house: it was well-maintained, it was centrally located, and it came with a roommate.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They enjoyed it so much, in fact, that they invited their sister Molly to live with them.
